Workspace Rules (Cursor)

Purpose
- These are workspace-level rules for Cursor AI.
- Keep the app dependency-free (Python stdlib API + static web), validate inputs, and preserve repo naming/ID patterns.

Global
- Python 3.10+, 4-space indents, type hints encouraged.
- No external network calls or packages; stdlib only.
- JSON keys snake_case; IDs: lst_00001, bid_00001, ask_00001, sal_00001.
- Endpoints mirror code style (e.g., /sales/settle_matched).
- Atomic writes to data/*.json, handlers non-blocking, all inputs validated.
- Frontend under web/ is pure HTML/CSS/JS; keep it fast, accessible, and mobile-first.

Testing
- Use pytest; add tests for new validation/ID logic, keep tests deterministic.

How to Use (Cursor)
- Open Cursor → AI → Rules → Workspace and enable the roles you need from .cursor/rules/.
- You can enable multiple roles at once (e.g., Project Manager + Frontend Engineer).

